By observing how this pension/social security system was made in Burkina Faso it's clear that the place of an unemployed and unable person is to wait for the asset of an employed person. This system multiplied by the patriotism I have for my homeland and me having no other place to go in case to fail my aspirations in Burkina Faso for some reasons, has shaped me who I am today.

And now I want to get back this money which I earned and deserve to be paid by me and my employer 17 years ago by volunteering for my homeland. Indeed I can't get this salary money guaranteed by my employer without working because I'm freelancer. I believe in my government but they still doubt my intensions toward the institution of Burkina Faso and its resources because the managed taxes do not for my knowledge allow them to move. That's why I'm relying on you to take my unfinished work all the way to the end. So by encouraging my aspiration you're not only helping me to get back this money controlled, by the CB ko (character building) to believe in my government and also to respect your money living in their purse. Anyhow thanks for having read my complete text and for also being interested in response to my proposition: helping me in order to make the national conscription bureaucracy clear for me.
